<LegalDoc 
	title="Privacy Policy" 
	description="Privacy policy and data handling practices for Alkalye."
	subtitle="Last updated: December 2025"
>
	<h2>Data Storage</h2>
	<p>Your documents are stored:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Locally on your device</li>
		<li>Optionally synced to the <a href="https://jazz.tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Jazz Cloud</a> when you create an account</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Encryption</h2>
	<p>Your data is end-to-end encrypted:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Encryption keys are derived from your passphrase</li>
		<li>Your passphrase is the only key to decrypt your data</li>
		<li>Neither we nor Jazz can access your documents</li>
		<li>When you share documents, collaborators can decrypt them using their own passphrases</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Analytics</h2>
	<p>We do not track you or collect analytics data.</p>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>For privacy concerns: <a href="mailto:assmann@hey.com" class="text-brand hover:underline">assmann@hey.com</a></p>
</LegalDoc>
